<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>The “Africa versus Europe” competition will be contested in the heavyweight, cruiserweight and super middleweight divisions. The event, which will feature a first and second leg, is co-promoted by Visser’s promoter Steve Kalakoda and his Croatia-based counterpart, Harry Gorian of Top Star International Promotions.For the tournament, Visser, who also holds African Boxing Union (SADC) belts, has been matched with 40-year-old Adnan Redzovic.Kalakoda says although his charge is not yet where they want him to be in terms of performance, they are happy with his showing on Friday night. “He is 30% of what he is going to be in the future but we are happy with his progress. “I’m very excited about Ruann, the performance he displayed on Friday night proves that teaming up with James Ali Bashir is bearing fruit,” said Kalakoda.“He used his jab perfectly and went to the body to slow the champion down from the third round, where the damage was done. He added pressure by moving forward. It was a good strategy, he followed his coach’s game plan,” he added.Kalokoda said they were grooming the youngster to be a big name in the division, that is why they brought in the American trainer. Ali Bashir has trained some the best heavyweights in the world such as Lennox Lewis, Alexandra Ysyk and Wladimir Klitshko.